Dear Hans,

I also agree that we have resolved the discrepancy between our UHF wave
functions, and we're working now to obtain the CCSD NOs using the Cs
symmetry-broken orbitals as a reference.  These NOs are obtained by
diagonalization of the spin-orbital density (including its UHF component),
and the occupations AJ has reported are the sum of the alpha and beta
contributions.  I think this is consistent with your approach.

Our stability code has gone through an overhaul in the last two weeks,
which has slowed our efforts further, but obtaining the data for this paper
is high on our priority list.  We'll let you know as soon as we have useful
results.

Best regards,

-Daniel

--
Prof. T. Daniel Crawford
crawdad@vt.edu

