> set of alpha and beta spin orbitals. The space parts are not orthogonal t=
o
> each other. Thus, they are difficult to interpret. The advantage of
> diagonalizing the total spin density matrix is that the resulting NOs ref=
er
> to the same basis. This question is more involved than I thought.
